            <div type="footnotes">
                <note xml:id="foot.f1"><ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_3026.xml">John Lubbock</ref> was CD’s neighbour; some of his land adjoined CD’s (<ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_2662.xml">Freeman 1978</ref>). Charlock is <hi rend="italic">Sinapis arvensis</hi>.</note>
                <note xml:id="foot.f2">In 1855, CD had investigated the length of dormancy and the vitality of charlock seeds, and he and Hooker had debated the issue of general seed viability at length (see <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_1581.xml"><hi rend="italic">Correspondence</hi></ref> vol. 5).</note>
